Package: houdini
Title: Programmatically Add Data Tables and Figures to Report Word Documents
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Aaron", "Godwood", email = "azmclaz@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A Shiny application for inserting tables and images
    at named bookmarks in a Word document template. Supports parameter and
    timeline filtering, interactive column/row exclusion, and produces a
    fully-formatted Word document with injected OOXML tables.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    shiny,
    rhandsontable,
    xml2,
    base64enc,
    zip,
    readxl,
    writexl
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    rstudioapi,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
